// index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>My Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css" />
    <script>
      console.log("Hello World! atul");
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>My Page</h1>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>


// main.css

* {
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box'
}

html, body {
    width: 100;
    font-size: 16px;
    background-color: #000;
    color: #fff;
}

main {
    height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
}

h1 {
    font-size: 250%;
}


// Steps for HTML and CSS
open VSCode
open ChromeDevTools
$ mkdir 02tut
$ code index.html			// creates new file at 02tut level

// HTML
! 					// Emmet shortcut HTML snippet
or type it out				// CS-50
inside <Head> element add <title> tag with text My Page
inside <Head> element add <script> tag with console.log("Hello World")
inside <Boby> element add <main> and <h1> tags with text My Page
save

// CSS
can put <style> element inside <head> section but not good idea
delete <style> tags	// now create css and then link to it from html link href
$ mkdir css		// create css folder at 02tut level
$ code main.css		// create main.css file inside css folder
in main.css, type out basic starting css boilerplate
in index.html, create link to href css/main.css

// Setup IDE VSCode, Terminal, DevTools
want VSCode File Explorer on left (Cntl B), VSCode Terminal below, on right Chrome DevTools 
in DevTools use CntlShiftD to switch docking position 
AltTab to focus on Chrome window then AltTab to focus on VSCode
CtnlB opens Terminal
$ start index.html	// open existing index.html from VSCode Terminal 
AltTab back to Chrome, CntlShiftI launches DevTools
multi-editor windows opened using CntlShiftTab then navigate using CntlArrow

// JavaScript		// to add JavaScript folder from Terminal
$ mkdir js		// at 02tut level
$ cd .. 		// to move up to file structure
$ cd 02tut
$ cd js			// now inside js folder
$ code main.js 		// create new file main.js
add comment and save to save file to file structure

grab and delete script statements for now
open Terminal, navigate to main.js file
back in editor, cut console.log("Hello World!"); code and paste into main.js file
back in index.html, add script scr tag

<script src=""
use VSCode to navigate and select main.js file
now <script src tags will link to main.js

add console.log("Hello World!"); 	// between <script> opening and closing tags

navigate to Terminal
$ start index.html

browser renders your web page, DevTools 
open blank Chrome webpage	about:blank
open Chrome DevTools Console

add code to main.js file	
	console.log("Hello World!");
	console.log(typeof "Atul");
	console.log(typeof 42);
	console.log(typeof true);
